e__content"><p>These instructions are provided for <strong>advanced users</=
strong>.</p><p>If you don=E2=80=99t understand these instructions, you shou=
ld not attempt to install custom plugins.</p><p>We do not provide support w=
ith custom plugins / installs, and you are responsible for any issues that =
may arise from using them.</p><p>If you run into issues and can=E2=80=99t f=
igure them out yourself, please stick to the <a href=3D"https://vencord.dev=
/download">official Vencord build</a>.</p></section></aside>
<h2 id=3D"prerequisite"><a href=3D"https://docs.vencord.dev/installing/cust=
om-plugins/#prerequisite">Prerequisite</a></h2>
<p>To add custom plugins, you need to build Vencord from source.</p>
<p>If you haven=E2=80=99t already done so, first follow the <a href=3D"http=
s://docs.vencord.dev/installing">Installing from Source</a> guide.</p>
<p>The following instructions assume you have already done so.</p>
<h2 id=3D"adding-plugins"><a href=3D"https://docs.vencord.dev/installing/cu=
stom-plugins/#adding-plugins">Adding plugins</a></h2>
<p>Open your Vencord folder. Inside it, you should find a folder called <co=
de dir=3D"auto">src</code>. This folder houses all of Vencord=E2=80=99s sou=
rce code.</p>
<p>If you don=E2=80=99t have this folder, you have not read the previous in=
structions. Go back and first follow the <a href=3D"https://docs.vencord.de=
v/installing">Installing from Source</a> guide.</p>
<h3 id=3D"creating-the-userplugins-folder"><a href=3D"https://docs.vencord.=
dev/installing/custom-plugins/#creating-the-userplugins-folder">Creating th=
e <code dir=3D"auto">userplugins</code> folder</a></h3>
<p>All official plugins are stored in the <code dir=3D"auto">src/plugins</c=
ode> folder.
However, unless you plan to <a href=3D"https://docs.vencord.dev/plugins/sub=
mission">submit your plugin to the official repository</a>, you should not =
put your plugin there, as you will run into conflicts.</p>
<p>Instead, you will want to use the <code dir=3D"auto">src/userplugins</co=
de> folder. This folder is reserved for custom / private plugins.</p>
<p>This folder won=E2=80=99t exist yet, so you=E2=80=99ll have to first cre=
ate it. Navigate to the <code dir=3D"auto">src</code> folder and create a n=
ew folder called <code dir=3D"auto">userplugins</code>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"adding-your-plugin"><a href=3D"https://docs.vencord.dev/installin=
g/custom-plugins/#adding-your-plugin">Adding your plugin</a></h3>
<p>Inside the <code dir=3D"auto">userplugins</code> folder, you can now add=
 your plugin.</p>
<p>Your plugin should be either a simple <code dir=3D"auto">myCoolPlugin.ts=
</code> or <code dir=3D"auto">myCoolPlugin.tsx</code> file, or a folder con=
taining an <code dir=3D"auto">index.ts</code> or <code dir=3D"auto">index.t=
sx</code> file.</p>
<p>Place it inside the previously created userplugins folder.</p>
